milestones.description: This is the highest match aggregate (610) involving teams England & Pakistan in ODIs
Graeme Hick has scored 32 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for ENG breaking Graham Gooch's record

stories.title: England snatch victory from jaws of defeat
stories.summary:
England snatched victory from the jaws of defeat to take a 1-0 lead in
the three-match one-day international series over Pakistan under
floodlights at the National Stadium here on Tuesday

stories.title: Flintoff rewarded for his driving skills
stories.summary: Andrew Flintoff was stunned when he was presented with a car following his match-winning innings at the National Stadium in Karachi

stories.title: Botham urges selectors to keep Flintoff
stories.summary: Ian Botham has urged England selectors to hang on to Andrew Flintoff for the rest of the Pakistan tour rather than send him home after his blistering innings in the first one-day intternational in Karachi

stories.title: England middle order dominate Pakistan attack to secure five-wicket win
stories.summary: An awesome display by England's batsmen brought a magnificent five-wicket victory, with 16 balls to spare, over Pakistan in the tour's first One Day International

stories.title: Awesome Flintoff powers England to stunning victory
stories.summary: Pakistan became the second side in six months to be 'Flintoffed' when England's young powerhouse charged the attack with a mesmerising 84 to steer his side to an historic victory in Karachi

stories.title: Hussain leads England fightback
stories.summary: Nasser Hussain demonstrated his return to form in Karachi when he led England's fightback against Pakistan following the controversial dismissal of Alec Stewart

stories.title: Fiery Flintoff sets England's tour hopes ablaze
stories.summary: An awesome display by England's batsmen achieved a magnificent five-wicket victory, with 16 balls to spare, over Pakistan in the tour's first One Day International
